<p>I have a management software hosted on a Windows Server 2003 machine, this software using an MS Access (*.mdb) database.</p>  <p>On another machine, that work with CentOS 6.7 I installed all the necessary modules relative to php odbc, freetds, etc..</p>  <p>Now I need to connect to my remote db using this PHP code:</p>  <pre><code>$db = new PDO("odbc:Driver=FreeTDS;Server=ip_of_windows_server;DBQ=mdb_file_name.mdb;Uid=;Pwd=my_mdb_password;");  $query = 'SELECT * FROM table_name'; $statement = $db-&gt;prepare($query); $statement-&gt;execute(); $result = $statement-&gt;fetchAll(PDO::FETCH_NUM); </code></pre>  <p>The error I got is:</p>  <pre><code>Fatal error: Uncaught exception 'PDOException' with message 'SQLSTATE[08001] SQLDriverConnect: 0 [unixODBC][FreeTDS][SQL Server]Unable to connect to data source' in /home/my_user/public_html/odbc/index.php:21 Stack trace: #0 /home/my_user/public_html/odbc/index.php(21): PDO-&gt;__construct('odbc:DRIVER=Fre...') #1 {main} thrown in /home/my_user/public_html/odbc/index.php on line 21 </code></pre>  <p>you can see that I don't use any username for my DB, but the same is if I type 'root' in the username.</p>  <p>The <code>Driver = FreeTDS</code> is taken from <code>etc/odbcinst.ini</code> with this content:</p>  <pre><code>[FreeTDS] Description = ODBC PDO Driver = /usr/local/freetds/lib/libtdsodbc.so Driver64 = /usr/lib64/libtdsodbc.so.0 UsageCount = 1 Threding = 2 </code></pre>  <p>and in <code>etc/odbc.ini</code> I have this content:</p>  <pre><code>[mydb] Description = "Microsoft Access Try DB" Driver = FreeTDS Database = /my_mdb_name.mdb Servername = ip_of_windows_server Port = 80 Trace = No TDS_Version = 8.0 </code></pre>  <p>I'm sure that I wrong something, but I don't know what :P</p>  <p>Thanks in advance.</p>